cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper proposes a metalearning approach for learning gradient-based reinforcement learning algorithms. The paper focuses on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The use of temporal convolutions and policy gradient methods suggests that it may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The application of the approach to randomized environments suggests that it may belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the use of metalearning suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
